commit ba61dde6730aa79f05450a8b56b22dbf528eb57c
Author: Javier Lopez <jlopex@cozybit.com>
Date:   Mon Mar 19 19:13:56 2012 -0700

    Fixes zeromq 2.1 not compiling on Android
    
    According to the libc documentation S_IWRITE is only for BSD
    compatibility:
    
    http://www.gnu.org/s/hello/manual/libc/Permission-Bits.html
    
    This patch adds a check to determine the target platform and
    use correct file access definition in each case:
    
    - For Linux and Android S_IWUSR is used.
    - For other platforms S_IWRITE is used.
    
    Signed-off-by: Javier Lopez <jlopex@cozybit.com>

 src/options.cpp |   10 +++++++---
 1 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

